    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1953-07-09T18:46:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1953-07-09T18:46:00-05:00" n="684"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d684">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">795.00/7–953: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in Korea</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d684fn1">This telegram, drafted by <persName
                            corresp="#p_JUA1">Johnson</persName> and cleared with <persName
                            corresp="#p_SWB1">Smith</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_DJF1"
                            >Dulles</persName>, was repeated to Pusan as telegram 31 and to Tokyo
                        for <persName corresp="#p_MRD1">Murphy</persName> and <persName
                            corresp="#p_CGMW1">Clark</persName> as 90. It was passed to the
                        Department of Defense for <persName corresp="#p_NFC1">Nash</persName> and
                        the <gloss target="#t_JCS1">JCS</gloss>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret<lb/>
                            <gloss target="#t_niact1">niact</gloss>
                        </hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1953-07-09T19:46:00-04:00"
                            >July 9, 1953—7:46 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>31. Reference your DTG 091600Z<note n="2" xml:id="d684fn2">
                        <hi rend="italic">
                            <ref target="#d684">Supra</ref>
                        </hi>.</note> and previous. While <persName corresp="#p_RS1"
                    >Rhee</persName>’s letter is not entirely satisfactory it represents great
                    progress from situation that existed at time you undertook your mission and
                    probably is about all we will be able obtain from him at this time. Rather than
                    negotiating and exchanging further correspondence on unsatisfactory portions his
                    letter, subject views yourself and <persName corresp="#p_CGMW1"
                    >Clark</persName>, believe we should tacitly consider his letter satisfactory
                    basis for entering into armistice, leaving detailed problems which it raises for
                    future discussion and negotiation.</p>
                <p>However concur on desirability joint US–<gloss target="#t_ROK1">ROK</gloss>
                    statement at time your departure along lines suggested your DTG 091125Z,<note
                        n="3" xml:id="d684fn3">Dated July 9, <ref target="#pg_1355">p.
                        1355</ref>.</note> and suggest efforts now being directed at obtaining
                        <persName corresp="#p_RS1">Rhee</persName>’s agreement to as satisfactory
                    joint statement as possible. Transmit text to Department prior release time so
                    that public relations aspects can be coordinated.</p>
                <pb facs="0245" n="1363" xml:id="pg_1363"/>
                <p>With regard to <persName corresp="#p_RS1">Rhee</persName>’s draft mutual security
                    treaty suggest you inform him Department immediately undertaking careful study
                    his draft and will be prepared conclude negotiations at high level meeting with
                    him to follow armistice.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DJF1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Dulles</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
